data.name: main_ButtonCopy.ToolTip
data.value:
Copy Results:
Click this button to add all of the generated words to your computer's clipboard. In other words, it's an automatic Ctrl+C! You'll then have to paste it somewhere else, like a document or other note-taking or text-based program.

data.name: main_ButtonRandom.ToolTip
data.value:
Hotkey: Spacebar, Enter
Use this button to generate a new batch of random names, taking into account all parameters set in the above controls, and replacing any words that have already been generated. In other words, if there are any words in the chart that you like but haven' yet saved, be sure to do so before you hit the Randomize! button again.
NOTE: You can still Randomize! without inputting any parameters in any of the other controls. It defaults to no prefix or suffix, a length of 3 syllable word fragments sampled from the entire unfiltered list, and only 1 name generated at a time.

data.name: checkRandomLastLetters.ToolTip
data.value:
Random Last Letter(s):
Checking this option is actually the same as leaving both text fields blank. All it does is ensure that the generated words will not consider any suffixes, whether filtered syllables or explicitly defined ones, when it constructs words. In other words, they will end with completely random syllables.

data.name: panelLastLetters.ToolTip
data.value:
Static Name Suffix:
Use this form to add exact letters to the end of the words you generate. These letters will not change or disappear unless you delete them from the box.
Last Letter(s) Generated:
Use this form to filter the list of syllable word fragments used by the generator to create the ending of the word. For example, entering the letter "a" will ensure the last portion of the word (before the suffix) begins with any syllable (from the list) that starts with "a," such as "an," "ath," "ar," or even just "a".

data.name: panelNameLength.ToolTip
data.value:
Hotkey: Left Arrow, Right arrow
Name Length:
The Random Name Generator constructs words by sampling from a massive list of pre-defined syllables (wordlist.txt). The word length is thus the number of times the generator randomly samples from that list to add more syllables. It then combines these word fragments with any defined prefixes or suffixes to produce names.
In other words, Name Length is the number of non-prefix and non-suffix syllable word fragments used when generating names.

data.value:
Random Length:
Checking this box will make each name generated use a random number (between 1 and 5) of syllable word fragments pulled from the list file. Use this option to get a lot more variety in the kinds of names you generate.
